{
  "text": "Studies in non-ASD pediatric samples suggest that GEXR may be beneficial for oppositional behavior in ADHD and for treatment of anxiety disorders [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A pilot study by Murphy and colleagues showed no difference between GEXR and placebo for the treatment of tics [CITATION_4] . The preliminary findings for oppositional behavior and anxiety are limited. Immediate-release alpha 2A -agonists, including guanfacine and clonidine, are commonly prescribed \"off label\" in pediatric populations to treat insomnia due to their sedating properties [CITATION_5] . However, a recent placebo-controlled study of GEXR in 29 children with ADHD and co-occurring sleep problems was terminated early after finding that GEXR was associated with decreased total sleep time on polysomnography compared with placebo [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
